project.name: tarlog-plugins
project.description:
DescriptionSet of small, but useful, features to Eclipse that I develop for my personal needs. Feel free to download and use this plugin.
Available featuresChange fonts size using shortcuts: Ctrl++ and Ctrl+- Open in Command Prompt - opens command prompt from the current file or folder in the Eclipse's Package Explorer/Navigator. Open in Windows Explorer - opens windows explorer with the selection on the current file or folder in the Eclipse's Package Explorer/Navigator. Templates for apache-commons-logging/slf4j. Release Notes1.3.1 Release NotesAdded support of Slf4j.
1.3 Release NotesChange fonts size using shortcuts. 1.2.3 Release NotesIssue 4 was fixed. 1.2.2 Release NotesIssue 3 was fixed. 1.2.1 Release NotesIssue 1 was fixed. Issue 2 was fixed. 1.2.0 Release NotesAdded templates for logging. 1.1.0 Release NotesOpen in Command Prompt - opens command prompt from the current file or folder in the Package Explorer/Navigator. Open in Windows Explorer - opens windows explorer with the selection on the current file or folder in the Package Explorer/Navigator. Mailing Lists/GroupsCurrently there are no mailing lists or groups for this project. I write updates about it to my blog. Feel free to ask questions in the comments.
